VISOR uses a Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) method for its reinforcement learning pipeline. This approach is designed to optimize the agent's performance by addressing dynamic context reconstruction and ensuring effective credit assignment during training. The training process involves a two-stage pipeline, starting with Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) followed by GRPO-based Reinforcement Learning (RL) to enhance retrieval precision and answer correctness.

