MM-Doc-R1 proposes the Similarity-based Policy Optimization (SPO) algorithm to address baseline estimation bias in multi-turn reinforcement learning (RL). SPO improves upon existing algorithms like GRPO by calculating a more accurate baseline through similarity-weighted averaging of rewards across multiple trajectories, rather than relying solely on the initial state’s baseline for all intermediate states. This approach enhances the stability and accuracy of the learning signal, leading to superior training performance.

